   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00009"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>In the early nineties, GSM was deployed in many European countries. Global System for Mobile communication offered for the first time international roaming for mobile subscribers. The GSM’s use of Time Division Multiple Access as its communication standard was debated at length. And every now and then there are big discussion whether Code Division Multiple Access should have been chosen over Time Division Multiple Access.
   </text>
  </text-unit>
